Nigerian Government on Friday directed the  assessment of a plant-based cough mixture as possible treatment for COVID-19. “The Federal Government has directed the National Agency for Food and Drug Administration and Control (NAFDAC) to carry out necessary procedures for the assessment of a plant-based cough mixture as a possible treatment for COVID-19,” Presidential spokesman Bashir Ahmed tweeted on Friday. Ahmed however did not mention which plant-based cough mixture will be assessed.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .